10
00:00:34,060 --> 00:00:35,820
but classical in particular,

11
00:00:35,820 --> 00:00:37,630
if it has an equilibrium state

12
00:00:37,630 --> 00:00:39,440
and you displace it from equilibrium,

13
00:00:39,440 --> 00:00:40,940
generally speaking,

14
00:00:40,940 --> 00:00:41,880
it will oscillate.

15
00:00:42,360 --> 00:00:45,140
It may oscillate with more than one frequency.

16
00:00:45,460 --> 00:00:46,360
For example,

17
00:00:46,360 --> 00:00:49,780
a violin string can oscillate in the fundamental range.

18
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:51,440
The fundamental frequency,

19
00:00:51,440 --> 00:00:53,080
the first harmonic,

20
00:00:53,080 --> 00:00:53,960
the second harmonic,

21
00:00:53,960 --> 00:00:55,740
and if you pluck it in odd ways,

22
00:00:55,740 --> 00:00:58,580
you can make some nasty noises,

23
